  "prompt": "How do you write a thesis statement on capital punishment?",
  "response": "Writing a thesis statement on capital punishment involves taking a clear position on the topic, which can either be in favor or against it, and providing a brief overview of the reasons supporting that position. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you craft an effective thesis statement:\n\n1. **Choose Your Position**: Decide on your stance regarding capital punishment. Are you for or against it? Your thesis statement should clearly reflect this position.\n\n2. **Identify Key Supporting Arguments**: Determine the main reasons for your position. These could be ethical considerations, effectiveness as a deterrent, cost implications, potential for wrongful convictions, etc.\n\n3. **Be Specific**: A strong thesis statement is specific and focused. Avoid vague language and ensure that it explicitly outlines the scope of your argument.\n\n4. **Combine Position and Reasons**: Integrate your position and key arguments into one or two coherent sentences. This will form the core of your thesis statement.\n\n5. **Revise for Clarity and Conciseness**: Ensure that your thesis statement is clear, direct, and concise. It should effectively convey your main argument and set the stage for further discussion.\n\nHere are a couple of examples of thesis statements on capital punishment:\n\n- **Against Capital Punishment**: \"Capital punishment should be abolished as it is an unethical practice that fails to deter crime, risks executing innocent people, and imposes a significant financial burden on the legal system.\"\n  \n- **In Favor of Capital Punishment**: \"Capital punishment serves as a necessary deterrent to heinous crimes, delivers justice to victims and their families, and upholds the principle of retributive justice when implemented with stringent safeguards against wrongful convictions.\"\n\nRemember, the strength of your thesis statement will often depend on the depth and breadth of the supporting arguments you plan to explore in your paper.",
